description: Lists the INFO, WARN, and ERROR events for periodic configuration updates performed by Application Insights. Examples of events represented are:

nested_items.name: EventList
nested_items.description: The list of configuration events and their corresponding details.

nested_items.name: ResourceGroupName
nested_items.description: The name of the resource group of the application to which the configuration event belongs.

nested_items.name: AccountId
nested_items.description: The Amazon Web Services account ID for the owner of the application to which the configuration event belongs.

nested_items.name: MonitoredResourceARN
nested_items.description: The resource monitored by Application Insights.

nested_items.name: EventStatus
nested_items.description: The status of the configuration update event. Possible values include INFO, WARN, and ERROR.

nested_items.name: EventResourceType
nested_items.description: The resource type that Application Insights attempted to configure, for example, CLOUDWATCH_ALARM.

nested_items.name: EventDetail
nested_items.description: The details of the event in plain text.

nested_items.name: EventResourceName
nested_items.description: The name of the resource Application Insights attempted to configure.

nested_items.name: NextToken
nested_items.description: The NextToken value to include in a future ListConfigurationHistory request. When the results of a ListConfigurationHistory request exceed MaxResults, this value can be used to retrieve the next page of results. This value is null when there are no more results to return.
